"title": "7908: baptism, significance of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7908: baptism, significance of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The NT uses a variety of images to explain the meaning of baptism, such as dying and rising with Christ, sharing in his death and being cleansed from sin.</p>\n<h2>Baptism is a symbol of the death of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:50\">LUK 12:50</a></strong> <em>Jesus Christ described his death as a baptism or a flood overwhelming him.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps42:7\">PSA 42:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:1-Ps69:2\">PSA 69:1–69:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps88:7\">PSA 88:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:38-Mark10:39\">MRK 10:38–10:39</a></p>\n<h2>Baptism is a symbol of the burial of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:3-Rom6:4\">ROM 6:3–6:4</a></strong> <em>Immersion in water symbolises how the old sinful life is buried with Christ.</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:13\">ROM 8:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:5\">COL 3:5</a></p>\n<h2>Baptism is a symbol of being saved from the flood</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:21\">1PE 3:21</a></strong> <em>The flood/baptism symbolises both judgment (the death of sinners and the death of Jesus Christ) and salvation (those in the ark and those in Christ passing safely through judgment).</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen7:6-Gen7:7\">GEN 7:6–7:7</a></p>\n<h2>Baptism is the gospel equivalent of circumcision</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:11-Col2:12\">COL 2:11–2:12</a></strong> <em>The “circumcision in Christ” may refer either to his death on the cross or to baptism.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:16\">DEU 10:16</a></p>\n<h2>Baptism recalls the exodus</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:1-1Cor10:2\">1CO 10:1–10:2</a></strong> <em>In and through the exodus experience Israel was united with and obedient to Moses, as Jesus Christ's people are to him.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:19-Exod14:24\">EXO 14:19–14:24</a></p>\n<h2>Baptism symbolises washing from sin</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:16\">ACT 22:16</a></strong> <em>Baptism is an outward sign of cleansing from sin and from a defiled life and conscience.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:11\">1CO 6:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:5\">TIT 3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:21\">1PE 3:21</a></p>\n<h2>Baptism is a symbol of putting on Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:27\">GAL 3:27</a></strong> <em>Baptism is seen as putting on Christ, as one might put on a coat or garment, and thus be “clothed with Christ”.</em></p>\n<h2>Baptism as a symbol of unity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:5\">EPH 4:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:13\">1CO 12:13</a></p>",
